0 ‚Äì Greeting and addressees</b></div></span></span><p></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>To
the teams at Archive.org, Creative Commons, the Electronic Frontier
Foundation, Open Rights Group, digital preservation networks, and
colleagues in space, research, and public institutions,</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>Thank
you for the work you do maintaining public memory, defending digital
rights, and exploring our shared universe. This email is addressed to
you collectively because the technology described below touches all
of your domains at once: long‚Äëterm archiving, human‚Äërights
documentation, governance of powerful tools, and the imagination
needed to think beyond existing institutional boundaries. It is
written with respect for your time and responsibilities, and with the
understanding that you receive many unusual proposals.</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>What
follows is not a request for funding, affiliation, or endorsement. It
is the presentation of a completed, live system that needs an
appropriate archival home and thoughtful readers. My hope is that
among you there are a few people willing to examine it on its own
terms and decide where it belongs in our shared record.</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<br />

</p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>Section
1 ‚Äì Why this technology breaks bottom‚Äëup reading</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>The
system I am sharing is a technology for constructing and
preserving¬†<span style="border: medium; display: inline-block; padding: 0cm;">top‚Äëdown
knowledge universes</span>¬†around vulnerable people and
public‚Äëinterest events. It is not a single tool, book, or
website, but an architecture: a way of arranging texts, code, media,
and receipts so that meaning emerges only when they are read in the
correct order, from the highest level of abstraction down to the most
painful concrete details.</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western" style="border: medium; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-align: center;">
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><span style="font-size: small;"><b>In
most institutional settings, evaluation happens¬†<span style="border: medium; display: inline-block; padding: 0cm;">bottom‚Äëup</span>.
A reader skims a few sentences, screenshots, or quotes, matches them
against familiar categories‚Äîdiagnosis, risk, reputation, political
cost‚Äîand then builds an interpretation from those fragments. This
approach is efficient for routine cases, but it is catastrophically
misaligned with the kind of work I have built. When applied to this
system, bottom‚Äëup reading does three things at once: it makes
the material look chaotic or grandiose; it hides the very safeguards
that prevent misuse; and it ensures that the technology fails to
