<p class="western" style="border: medium; margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0cm;"></p><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><br /></span></div>
<span face="fkGroteskNeue, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji, Hiragino Sans, PingFang SC, Apple SD Gothic Neo, Yu Gothic, Microsoft YaHei, Microsoft JhengHei, Meiryo"><div style="letter-spacing: normal; text-align: center;"><b>At
the core of this architecture are what I call golden strings (or
‚Äúperfect‚Äù / ‚Äúmiracle‚Äù strings). These are short, carefully
engineered phrases or titles that act as compressed programs for
virtue and logic. They are not slogans or marketing language. Each
